<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="257" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,152,359]" pageId="6" pageNumber="257">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,152,179]" pageId="6" pageNumber="257">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male genitalia characters were described based on the new species and the drawing of the genital capsule of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Evans, 1942)" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1942" baseAuthorityName="Evans" baseAuthorityYear="1942" box="[273,566,189,215]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pettya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="257" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctata">
<emphasis box="[273,398,190,215]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="257">P. punctata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Evans, J. W." box="[413,557,189,215]" pageId="6" pageNumber="257" pagination="27 - 30" refId="ref3347" refString="Evans, J. W. (1942) New leaf-hoppers from Tasmania and Queensland. Paper and Proceedings of the Royal Society of Tasmania, 1941, 27 - 30." type="journal article" year="1942">Evans, 1942</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. The male genitalia of the 
<typeStatus box="[864,912,189,215]" pageId="6" pageNumber="257">type</typeStatus>
species and the other previously included species, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Kirkaldy, 1906)" authorityName="Kirkaldy" authorityYear="1906" baseAuthorityName="Kirkaldy" baseAuthorityYear="1906" box="[208,505,225,252]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pettya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="257" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="taedea">
<emphasis box="[208,311,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="257">P. taedea</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kirkaldy, G. W." box="[325,498,225,252]" pageId="6" pageNumber="257" pagination="271 - 479" refId="ref3432" refString="Kirkaldy, G. W. (1906) Leaf-hoppers and their natural enemies. (Pt. IX Leaf-hoppers. Hemiptera). Report of work of the Experi- ment Station of the Hawaiian Sugar Planters' Association. Division of Entomology bulletin, 1 (9), 271 - 479." type="journal article" year="1906">Kirkaldy, 1906</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, have not been studied. This genus is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Dworakowska, 1972" authorityName="Dworakowska" authorityYear="1972" box="[1039,1365,225,251]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Eldama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="257" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1039,1126,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="257">Eldama</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Dworakowska, I." box="[1133,1365,225,251]" pageId="6" pageNumber="257" pagination="395 - 405" refId="ref3267" refString="Dworakowska, I. (1972) On some oriental Erythroneurini (Auchenorrhyncha, Cicadellidae, Typhlocybinae). Bulletin de l'Academie Polonaise des Sciences, Serie des Sciences Biologiques, 20 (6), 395 - 405." type="journal article" year="1972">Dworakowska, 1972</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
externally, but the pits on pronotum are larger and sparser, the subgenital plate is not pointed apically and has macrosetae subbsasally, and the preapical lobe of the style is much larger.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
